<Layout frontmatter={metadata}>

<p><em>Last Updated: March 2026</em></p>

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>Address.Makeup ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our Service.</p>

<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> Names, email addresses, and business details provided via setup forms.</li>
    <li><strong>Business Data:</strong> Public business info, including studio names and Google Business Profile links.</li>
    <li><strong>Payment Data:</strong> Handled via third-party processors (PayPal). We do not store financial info on our servers.</li>
    <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> Standard log info (IP addresses) collected via analytics tools to improve performance.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Governing Law</h2>
<p>This Privacy Policy and our privacy practices are governed by the laws of <strong>the State of Delaware, United States</strong>, without regard to its conflict of law principles. Any legal actions related to this Policy shall be brought exclusively in the state or federal courts located in Delaware.</p>

<h2>4. Disclosure of Information</h2>
<p>We do not sell your personal data. We only share info with vendors necessary for hosting and payment processing, or if required by law.</p>

<h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
<p>You may request access to or deletion of your data at any time. To exercise these rights, please contact us directly.</p>

<h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us through our <a href="/contact">Contact Page</a>.</p>

</Layout>
